[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Flux Context has gotten an update on Open Art and we\'re going to jump right into it. First and foremost, under model, make sure you have Flux Context selected. And under the prompt box, you\'ll see the Omni reference area here.'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'You want to click on this. And now you\'ll see that you can use up to four images to compose your scene. If you happen to be new to Open Art or you\'re new to Flux context, make sure to check'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'out this video here. I go more in depth on how the model works. Now, we\'re going to start with something super simple. And I\'m going to bring in the Open Art logo. And we\'re simply going to put it'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'on a black t-shirt. And I already have an image that I\'ve previously generated. That\'s the one right there. And within the prompt box, my prompt is place the white logo and text on the left chest of'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the woman\'s black t-shirt. I found that if I just put logo, it would just put the logo. So, you have to be very specific. Just a reminder with Flux context, you have to almost be very'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'literal with it. Be sure to turn off autoenhance, otherwise it\'s going to spice up your prompt. You definitely don\'t want that for something as simple as this. And for this image, I think I\'m'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'going to go 2x3. Go ahead and generate the image. And a result of using those two reference images and the prompt, we get this nice result of the logo on the black t-shirt. As previously mentioned,'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'if you just mention logo, it may just put the logo. And currently, this is still a beta product. So, you might see something like this where for whatever reason, it just didn\'t recognize the transparency. And as we saw in previous'

[01:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'examples in the other video, the logo sometimes would come out bigger, but actually doesn\'t look too bad when it\'s across the chest there. So now let\'s'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
